messages.message: Hey its quite confusing that we return a `FAIL` when your validation script isn’t valid. It makes it seem like its valid and returning fail. Can we return `ERROR` if the script is broken instead?

hm, I’ll defer to Elan and Weiming here — my perspective is that we do actually want to show “Fail” here because that is how this would show up in the app results, but i agree we should make it more obvious that the error exists in the code
This is being worked on. From design end there are mocks https://instabase.atlassian.net/browse/EPD-1969 (there are 2 linked design tickets: 1. Build (exactly your case @Lee and 2. Review)
